			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #020A0F;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												I was looking for groundspawns for my epic in the caves in DN.  I guess I tripped a trap somewhere down there, because a construct came after me.<br><br>I faded no less than five times (all my mana would permit) down there.  Each time I was well ahead of the construct and out of its line of sight.  When I faded the Chetari stopped chasing me (so apparently it partially worked) but the construct could not be ditched by any means.  A few seconds after fading, the construct would charge around the corner, still aggroed, and hit me for a little more damage before I could get distance from it again.<br><br>Why would this happen?  There was no way the construct could see me, and I should have been outside its aggro radius when I faded.<br><br>As far as I'm able to tell from this experience, either FM needs to be fixed or the documentation for FM needs to be fixed.  If it's the latter, I'd appreciate somebody explaining the secret rule by which FM failed and got me killed tonight.
																		
