												It's actually kind of funny, because I had been thinking how I never had any problems fading trap spawns off me in Akheva.  They see invis, but as long as I can get around a corner where they don't have LOS on me, just for an instant, they go away like I expected the constructs would.<br><br>Of course, it's been a number of months since I've been to Akheva, so I wonder if this is something that's been broken between then and now, that at least some see invis mobs are no longer having to make a LOS check before reaggroing.<br><br>Or maybe it's that LOS calculations are broken yet again, at least in some zones.  Sometimes it seems there's no happy medium between "MOBs can hit you through a wall" and "you can't hit a clearly visible MOB over a speed bump between you and it."  The former, combined with a MOB having very large reaction radius, would indeed result in inexplicably unshakable MOBs.
																		
