			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Well maybe in DN it wasnt bug, but since OoW there a few things that itch my mind. I never really investigated, but here some weird si tuation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But first off, i have to say that I use a Fade macro that make stop attack and sing before i fade.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I dont know if its my memory thats wrong or not, but the way i remember Fade to work is if you are in a middle of a lot of monster that dont see invis and you fade, they ran off. Recently though, it seem that when you <STRONG>fade</STRONG> the mobs continue a bit of there attack on you, like finishing there melee round or something. In another word, it break your invis and keep wacking you. So since OoW i have to get out of melee range of any mob before fading or they got an "extra" melee round on me. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Second situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This happen most often in Muramite Provinground. As most of you know there is several circle room in there with 3 spawn in it. So here is what I do and the weird result. Usually the mob you want is the center one cause its the PH. So I target the first add, Snare or Mez it. target 2nd Add and Snare or Mez it. There I have only the PH mob (or named) running far from the other mobs. When i am at about 2-3 (sometime 4) time the mob aggro range i <STRONG>fade</STRONG>. Boastful Bellow&nbsp;very quickly (see why above)&nbsp;the ph and then pull it to camp that is 1 or 2 time the aggro range away.&nbsp; Then we have 1 mob in camp and we all happy, i hope. Why hope ? Cause once in a while the w add just come to the camp anyway.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Third situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think this one might be intended, but not sure. Sometimes you aggro a mob drag it near camp. Then as soon you <STRONG>fade </STRONG>the mob<STRONG> </STRONG>just&nbsp;warp back to his spawn location. What is even weirder is the fact that in the process the mob aggro list seem to be wiped. Also, i have noticed that if you had snared the mob it usually dont warp (either snare is still active or not). So maybe the mob aggro list fade with time.. i dont know.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Like I said i never really investigate, but those 3 situations happen often with OoW.</DIV>
																		
